get_minibatch_size(size_of_eg:int, num_available_egs:int, input_ended:bool) → intÂ¶

This function tells you what minibatch size should be used for this eg.

Parameters:
  • size_of_eg (int) â The size of the eg, as obtained by GetNnetExampleSize()
  • num_available_egs (int) â The number of egs of this size that are currently available
  • input_ended (bool) â True if the input has ended. False otherwise
Returns:

Minibatch Size to use in this situation
